# Fedora Workstation – Technical Evaluation

## Overview
Fedora is a Red Hat–sponsored distribution with a strong focus on innovation, stability, and modern Linux technologies.

## Installation Experience
- Very polished installation interface.
- GNOME desktop smooth and responsive.

## Strengths
- Cutting-edge software.
- Excellent developer ecosystem.
- Strong SELinux integration for security.

## Limitations
- Faster release cycle requires more updates.
- Not ideal for long-term enterprise systems.

## Best Use Cases
✓ Developers  
✓ Linux learners  
✓ GNOME desktop users  
✓ Testing modern features

